 that in H-ATLAS the specific star\nformation rate anticorrelates with stellar mass and reaches values as high as\nin our Galaxy. On the other hand HeViCS ETG appear to have little star\nformation. Based on the trends found here, H-ATLAS ETG are thought to have more\nextended star formation histories and a younger stellar population than HeViCS\nETG.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 May 2015 13:46:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
